     <div type="clarification">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <p>
      <hi>J</hi> Would haue the Reader aduerti<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sed, that whereas in one place of this boke, I haue these woords: <hi>The Authour to the Hebrewes speake of cer<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>taine Christians, which were racked, &amp;c.</hi> My meaning was not, but that I iud<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ged him to speake especially of those which suffered persecution, before the comming of Christ in the fleshe: which beleuing in Christ to come, may also well be called by the name of <hi>Chrstians.</hi> Yet after it was printed, I suspecting that it might be an occa<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sion of cauilling to some: I thought good to sett downe a word or two of my meaning therin.</p>
</div>
